22Global%20Tensions%2C%20Climate%20Crisis%20Push%20Doomsday%20Clock%20Closest%20To%20Catastrophe%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20global%20tensions%20rise%20and%20climate%20threats%20loom%2C%20the%20Doomsday%20Clock%2C%20a%20symbol%20of%20humanity's%20precarious%20position%2C%20has%20been%20moved%20to%2089%20seconds%20before%20midnight%20-%20the%20closest%20it's%20ever%20been%20to%20a%20catastrophe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20alarming%20shift%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bwarning%26quot%3B%20from%20a%20panel%20of%20international%20scientists%2C%20who%20cite%20a%20range%20of%20escalating%20threats%2C%20including%20Russia's%20nuclear%20threats%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20rising%20military%20tensions%20in%20global%20hotspots%2C%20the%20military%20use%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20and%20the%20worsening%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bulletin%20of%20the%20Atomic%20Scientists%2C%20which%20created%20the%20clock%20in%201947%20during%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20set%20the%20time%20closer%20to%20the%20theoretical%20point%20of%20annihilation%20-%20one%20second%20closer%20than%20last%20year.%20The%20closer%20the%20clock%20is%20to%20midnight%2C%20the%20more%20danger%20there%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20setting%20the%20Clock%20one%20second%20closer%20to%20midnight%2C%20we%20send%20a%20stark%20signal%3A%20Because%20the%20world%20is%20already%20perilously%20close%20to%20the%20precipice%2C%20a%20move%20of%20even%20a%20single%20second%20should%20be%20taken%20as%20an%20indication%20of%20extreme%20danger%20and%20an%20unmistakable%20warning%20that%20every%20second%20of%20delay%20in%20reversing%20course%20increases%20the%20probability%20of%20global%20disaster%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Board%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebulletin.org%2Fdoomsday-clock%2F2025-statement%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Holz%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20Bulletin's%20science%20and%20security%20board%2C%20said%20the%20factors%20shaping%20this%20year's%20decision%20were%20the%20same%20as%202024's%2C%20but%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20seen%20insufficient%20progress%20in%20addressing%20the%20key%20challenges%2C%20and%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20this%20is%20leading%20to%20increasingly%20negative%20and%20worrisome%20effects.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSetting%20the%20Doomsday%20Clock%20at%2089%20seconds%20to%20midnight%20is%20a%20warning%20to%20all%20world%20leaders%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2025%2Fjan%2F28%2Fdoomsday-clock-closer-than-ever-to-midnight%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20full-scale%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20which%20began%20with%20Russia's%202022%20invasion%2C%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20major%20source%20of%20nuclear%20risk.%20The%20conflict%20could%20escalate%20into%20a%20nuclear%20conflict%20at%20any%20moment%20due%20to%20a%20rash%20decision%2C%20or%20through%20an%20accident%20or%20miscalculation%2C%20according%20to%20Mr%20Holz.%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20decision%20to%20lower%20the%20threshold%20for%20a%20nuclear%20strike%20in%20response%20to%20conventional%20attacks%20adds%20to%20the%20danger.%20This%20change%20in%20doctrine%2C%20outlined%20in%20November%202022%2C%20sets%20the%20conditions%20under%20which%20Putin%20could%20authorise%20the%20use%20of%20Russia's%20massive%20nuclear%20arsenal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20reluctant%20to%20discuss%20a%20new%20nuclear%20arms%20treaty%20with%20the%20US%2C%20as%20the%20New%20Strategic%20Arms%20Reduction%20Treaty%20(START)%20is%20set%20to%20expire%20in%202026.%20Mr%20Holz%20said%20that%20tensions%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20including%20with%20Iran%2C%20remain%20dangerously%20unstable%2C%20and%20he%20also%20pointed%20to%20other%20volatile%20regions%20like%20Taiwan%20and%20North%20Korea.%20He%20warned%20that%20any%20of%20these%20could%20escalate%20into%20a%20conflict%20involving%20nuclear%20powers%2C%20with%20%26quot%3Bunpredictable%20and%20potentially%20devastating%20outcomes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20from%20the%20bulletin%20also%20highlights%20the%20intensifying%20climate%20crisis%2C%20with%20the%20past%20year%20being%20recorded%20as%20the%20hottest%20in%20history%2C%20according%20to%20the%20UN%20World%20Meteorological%20Organisation.%20The%20report%20also%20points%20out%20the%20dangers%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20biological%20science%20misuse%2C%20along%20with%20the%20spread%20of%20misinformation%20and%20conspiracy%20theories%20fuelled%20by%20technological%20advancements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20grim%20warnings%2C%20there%20is%20hope.%20Juan%20Manuel%20Santos%2C%20former%20president%20of%20Colombia%20and%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%20laureate%2C%20said%20there%20was%20still%20time%20to%20make%20the%20right%20choices%20to%20turn%20back%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20Doomsday%20Clock%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F01%2F28%2Fus%2Fdoomsday-clock-2025.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Bulletin%2520of%2520the%2520Atomic%2Cthe%2520misuse%2520of%2520artificial%2520intelligence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20urged%20world%20leaders%20to%20act%20swiftly%20and%20wisely%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BEvery%20second%20counts.%20Let%20us%20use%20each%20one%20wisely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738143480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-01%2Frr43qnno_doomsday-clock-reuters-650_625x300_25_January_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fglobal-tensions-climate-crisis-push-doomsday-clock-closest-to-catastrophe-7585775%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Doomsday%20Clock%20is%20a%20symbolic%20representation%20of%20the%20threat%20of%20human%20extinc